roaches to the designing such interfaces. A multimodal interface for mobile devices requires the integration of several recognition technologies together with sophisticated user interface and distinct tools for input and output of data. The book will address the challenge of designing devices in a synergetic fashion which does not burden the user or to create a technological overload.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aMobile computing. 0aMultimodal user interfaces (Computer systems). 4acomputertechnik. 4aelecktrotechnik. 4aspeech technology. 4asprachverarbeitung. 7aTechnology & Engineering / Electrical.2bisacsh  amobile speech.  amultimodal computing.  amultimodal mobile devices.  aspeech processing.1 aAgarwal, Sanjay, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArtelt, Detlev, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAsherov, Ron, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrown, Kathy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrown, Kathy.1 aCarbaugh, Donal, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChakraborty, Abir, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDahl, Deborah A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDahl, Deborah.1 aDegani, Asaf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDegani, Asaf.1 aHeymann, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJoshi, Prashant, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLawo, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLawo, Michael.1 aLie, Sunny, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLogan, Robert K., econtributor.4ctb